 LESS RELEVANT THAN A CEREAL BOX  &HT;     By SCOTT OSTLER 
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Love letters straight from your heart, keep us
so near while apart...
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Thanks for a column that is usually entertaining, though &LR; 
 &UR; sometimes tedious. (Ken Buhagiar) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   This one is tedious already.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Why does this guy have a column? What an idiotic series &LR; 
 &UR; of meaningless crap. I've read cereal boxes that had more &LR; 
 &UR; relevance to my life. It sounds like a stupid man's cocktail &LR; 
 &UR; party conversation. Even when it seems he's onto an actual idea &LR; 
 &UR; or worthwhile commentary he doesn't follow through. Lose him. &LR; 
 &UR; (Dean Hughes) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Hi! What's your sign?
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Please, someone write back to me because I am dying to &LR; 
 &UR; know. Did you go to a California Public School? I read your &LR; 
 &UR; column daily, and that is probably the average amount of times I &LR; 
 &UR; see an error. Daily. Grammatical, historical, political ... you &LR; 
 &UR; name it, you've done it. (Jenny Maher) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   I make the mistakes other columnists are afraid to make. And for
the record, I did attend public school _ Mick Jagger High School in
Chowchilla.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; I am sorry to hear of your complete and total ignorance of the &LR; 
 &UR; laws of the United States. If you hate guns so much, why do you &LR; 
 &UR; live in a country that protects the right to keep and bear arms &LR; 
 &UR; for its citizens? Perhaps you should go elsewhere if you will &LR; 
 &UR; not support the Constitutional rights of Americans. &LR;
