   &UR; U.S. AMBASSADOR DIRECTED ISRAEL'S BOMBARDMENT OF LEBANON &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ISRAEL-US-WARMONGERS-EXCLUSIVE-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BSALIM, LEBANON _ Did the American ambassador to Israel decide
the target of Israel's bombing of Lebanon last Friday? Incredible
as it seems, Martin Indyck's intervention appears to have done just
that. The leak of Indyck's intervention, via impeccable diplomatic
sources, is remarkable. That a U.S. ambassador can, in effect,
decide the target site of Israel's bombs is one thing. But Indyck
also happens to be the former head of AIPAC, the most powerful
Jewish-Israeli lobby group in the United States....By Robert Fisk,
The Independent, London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (EXCLUSIVE...Attn. Commentary Editors) &QL;
