   &UR; `SWITCH OFF OR GET LOST': SAN FRANCISCO BANS CELL PHONES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CELLPHONE-BACKLASH-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Ed Moose knew the cell-phone craze had gone too
far when one customer at his trendy San Francisco restaurant picked
up the phone to talk to another customer sitting at the other end
of the bar. This was more than Moose could stand, so he took
action: he banned cell phones from his establishment altogether.
The cellular crowd has now been banished to the pavement, along
with that other group of Californian outcasts, smokers. ``There's a
total backlash going on,'' said the bar manager at Dine, a
restaurant in San Francisco's so-called Multimedia Gulch area,
where everyone has a cell phone but nobody is allowed to use them
anymore....By Andrew Gumbel, The Independent, London &QL;
</P>
