<HEADLINE>
DOUGLAS FAIRBANKS JR.: SON OF ZORRO 
</HEADLINE>
  Includes a 350-word sidebar 
 By GAYDEN WREN  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   In an era when practically everyone in Hollywood seems to be the
child of a former star, a special distinction belongs to Douglas
Fairbanks Jr., the suave, sophisticated actor who was the first
second-generation movie star.
</P>
<P>
   Despite a lifetime of accomplishments onscreen and off,
Fairbanks never quite shook the ``Jr.'' from his name, always
remaining slightly in his father's shadow. But when he died on May
7 at 90, the entertainment world lost one of its most popular and
long-lived fixtures.
</P>
<P>
   Though there was a marked resemblance between the two, Fairbanks
never had the flamboyant exuberance which distinguished his
father's best films. Instead, he was debonair and casually
