<HEADLINE>
O.J., MINUS PHONE RECORDS, CAN BE REACHED HERE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What is the mailing address of O.J. Simpson?
</P>
<P>
   _ B.P.D., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Simpson in care of attorney Leroy ``Skip'' Taft,
11999 San Vicente Blvd., No. 340, Los Angeles, CA 90049.
</P>
<P>
   In April, a federal judge dismissed a lawsuit filed by Simpson
for access to telephone records from the home of Nicole Brown
Simpson on June 12, 1994, the day she and Ron Goldman were
murdered.
</P>
<P>
   Simpson, who was acquitted of murder but found liable for the
deaths in a civil trial, claims the phone records will prove his
innocence.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Simpson's Heisman Trophy and 80 other items were sold
at auction for $430,000. The money was used to pay some of the
$33.5 million civil judgment owed by Simpson to Nicole Brown
Simpson's estate and to Ron Goldman's parents.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find basket-weave stockings?
</P>
<P>
   _ P.A., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: The mail-order retailer Feeling USA in Hollywood, Fla., sells
Lycra basket-weave pantyhose for $6.90 as item No. Q9902.
</P>
<P>
   To order, call (877) 293-3393 or visit the Web site
www.feelingusa.com. The company sells lingerie, costumes and other
items.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to the actor David Birney?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.C., Montgomery, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Birney in care of DGRW, 1501 Broadway, Suite 703,
New York, NY 10036, or visit his Web site, www.davidbirney.com.
</P>
<P>
   In recent years, the 61-year-old actor has toured with ``The
Diaries of Adam &AMP; Eve,'' a play that he adapted, directed and stars
in. The play, based on two Mark Twain stories, was performed in
1988 for broadcast on the PBS series ``American Playhouse.''
</P>
<P>
   He also has appeared in episodes of ``Poltergeist: The Legacy''
and ``Star Trek: Deep Space Nine.''
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
