<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-HUMANTRAFFIC-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`TRAFFIC' COUNTERS FAMILIARITY OF ITS STORY LINE BY BEING FUN TO
WATCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT PHILPOT 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Human Traffic'' introduces its main characters as if they were
power chords, slamming their names up on the screen in big, bold
fonts before each tells us a little about himself or herself.
They're all frustrated _ by their jobs, by their sex lives _ and,
to paraphrase the Easybeats, they've got Friday on their minds.
</P>
<P>
   Actually, it is Friday, and Jip, Lulu, Koop, Nina and Moff are
gearing up for a tension-releasing lost weekend on the rave scene
in Cardiff, Wales. Each has a problem that will be worked out, at
least in part, by the film's end, sometimes with their friends'
help. Their woes aren't anything new, but rookie feature director
Justin Kerrigan _ a 25-year-old vet of the rave scene himself _
films them with freshness and almost exhaustive energy.
</P>
<P>
   Kerrigan kicks out the jams here, throwing in fantasy sequences
and hallucinatory moments as his heroes drink, dance and drug their
way through Friday and Saturday before hitting the Sunday-afternoon
comedown, complete with amusingly uncomfortable moments with their
parents. The whole movie seems pumped and _ unlike its American
counterpart, the upcoming ``Groove'' _ counters the familiarity of
its story line simply by being fun to watch. The blasts of
electronica music might offend sensitive ears, and the lives of the
proletarian characters aren't steeped in a lot of depth, but with
this ``Traffic'' traveling at 90 mph, it's hard to care about any
bumps in the road.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Film: ``Human Traffic''
</P>
<P>
   Rating: 3 1/2 on a 1-5 scale
</P>
<P>
   Director: Justin Kerrigan
</P>
<P>
   Length: 100 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Rated: R
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Robert Philpot is film critic for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
