</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-SLAYING (TIMBERON, N.M.) _ The man accused of killing a
Texas A&AMP;M University student last month after posing as a woman on
the Internet has ``a terrible rage problem,'' chronic medical
ailments and sexuality issues, his father says. By JOHN GONZALEZ.
</P>
<P>
   METHODISTS (Cleveland, Ohio) _ The United Methodist general
conference comes to a temporary halt Thursday as gay rights
activists in the convention hall protest the church's anti-gay
position. BY RICHARD VARA.
</P>
<P>
   RAILROAD-KILLER (Houston) _ The sister of admitted serial killer
Angel Maturino Resendiz testifies that she did not solicit reward
money for convincing her brother to turn himself in to Texas
Rangers. However, under cross-examination, she admits that in fact
she took the $86,000 in rewards. Also, Resendiz' mother tells
jurors that Angel was abused as a child. BY LISA TEACHEY.
</P>
