<P>
   ON THE BOULEVARD
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Here are details about visiting some downtown
attractions on or near Houston Street in Manhattan:
</P>
<P>
   Night Life
</P>
<P>
   CHAOS, 225 E. Houston St., at Essex Street, (212) 475-3200.
Jesse Sprague, a D.J., Friday night and Saturday at 10. Cover, $20;
no minimum.
</P>
<P>
   MADAME X, 94 W. Houston St., between Thompson Street and
LaGuardia Place, (212) 539-0808.
</P>
<P>
   MERCURY LOUNGE, 217 E. Houston St., between Ludlow and Essex
Streets, (212) 260-4700. Friday night: The Blue Benn, 7:30; Extra
Virgin, 8:30; Mannix, 9:30; Jesse Dayton and the Road Kings, 10:30.
Cover: $8. Saturday: the Rev. Horton Heat and Los Straitjackets at
8 p.m.; $10 cover.
</P>
<P>
   MEOW MIX, 269 E. Houston St., between Avenues A and B, (212)
254-0688. Friday night: Faint Red Trees at 9, DJ Frida at 10:30,
$5. Saturday, Fraggle Rock Party: Pacman, at 9 p.m.; the Karyn Kuhl
Experience, at 10 p.m.; Fraggle Rock House Band's tribute to
Michael Jackson at 11 p.m.; then D.J. Snoopy and BK Brewster.
Admission: $8 ($5 with flyer available at Meow Mix).
</P>
<P>
   S.O.B.'s, 204 Varick St., near West Houston, (212) 243-4940.
Friday night: Soca with Sam, at 9; a Haitian band called Strings,
at midnight and 2 a.m.; $20 cover. Saturday: Brazilian Music Night,
Ogans playing at 8, 10 and midnight, and a percussion samba band,
the Manhattan Samba Group, Anvil FX with Andrea Marque, at 2 a.m.;
$20 for Ogan; $10 for Anvil FX. Sunday is the Bossa Nova brunch for
Mother's Day, shows at 1 and 4 p.m.; noon and 3 p.m. seatings,
$32.95, $9.95 for children 12 and younger.
</P>
<P>
   SOHO BILLIARDS, 298 Mulberry St., near East Houston Street,
(212) 925-3753. Hours, Mondays through Fridays, 11 a.m. to 3 a.m.;
Saturdays and Sundays, 11 a.m. to 4 a.m. Hourly rates begin at $7
and increase according to day, time and number of players.
</P>
<P>
   ZINC BAR, 90 W. Houston St., between LaGuardia Place and
Thompson Street, (212) 477-8337. Friday night: Nkossi Konda and
Peace of Mind, lively Afro-Caribbean percussion, at 11, 12:30 and 2
a.m., $5 cover. Saturday, same times, is Brazilian music by
Marianne Ebert.
</P>
