<P>
   DELL-EARNINGS _ Earnings to be released after the markets close.
Paying close attention to performance in Europe, a soft spot, and
possible part shortages. (Pletz, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   FORD-EUROPE _ ATLANTA _ Ford execs, including CEO Nasser, sit
behind a bamboo desk at Zoo Atlanta and discuss what the company's
doing to straighten out a money-losing situation in Europe. Also,
Ford said it is concerned about the effect of sports utility
vehicles on the environment and on road safety. (Grantham, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   ROBERDS _ Roberds, which closed all its Georgia stores last
week, is planning to start its liquidation sale next Friday. A
bankruptcy court in Ohio will decide Monday which liquidation firm
will handle the sale and its length. Meanwhile, customer orders
made after January 19, the date Roberds filed for Chapter 11
bankruptcy protection, will get top priority but the timetable for
when they'll get their stuff remains unclear. (DeGross, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   HDEPOT-BIAS _ Five Fort Lauderdale Home Depot employees have
sued the company for discrimination. (Bond, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Now that both sides in the Microsoft
antitrust trial have proposed their solutions, it's possible to
picture what the software world would look like in a couple of
years if one or the other became reality. (Glass, Cox News
Service).
</P>
