<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-WEST-PREVIEW _ The Dallas Stars are trying to win a second
straight Stanley Cup, but the NHL's hotest team stands in their
way. The Stars play the Colorado Avalanche in the Western
Conference Finals beginning Saturday in a matchup that hockey fans
have been dreaming about all season. Many experts call it the real
Stanley Cup Finals. Eastern Conference rivals Philadelphia and New
Jersey are almost being ignored. That series starts Sunday.
(Schultz, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO RACING
</P>
<P>
   Following is a budget for this week's Inside NASCAR page.
</P>
<P>
   EDITORS NOTE: WINSTON CUP HAS AN OFF WEEK IN OBSERVANCE OF
MOTHER'S DAY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET INSIDE NASCAR 00512: STEWART'S SOPHOMORE JINX _ If there
is such a thing as a sophomore jinx on the Winston Cup circuit,
Tony Stewart is living it. Heralded during his rookie season as
perhaps the best up-and-coming driver the circuit had seen since
Richard Petty, Stewart hasn't won a thing in 2000. His hard luck
continued at Richmond where bad luck hit once again. (Minter,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
