<P>
   NEW ORLEANS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW ORLEANS _ One of my favorite things about New Orleans is
that it never seems to change. Every time I visit, I know I will
stroll through the French Quarter, eat brunch at Commander's Palace
and a muffuletta at Central Grocery and a Lucky Dog from a pushcart
vendor, and ride the streetcar through the magnolia-lined Garden
District, stopping to wander past the stately mansions. But before
this visit, I'd heard the city was changing so much: There was a
new flashy Harrah's casino. Several big new hotels, including two
oh-so-chic Ws. Hot new restaurants that didn't serve traditional
creole food. A theme park. Two new museums. Was it still going to
feel like New Orleans? By PATRICIA RODRIGUEZ. Story has moved in
``t'' travel category. (Accompanied by NEW ORLEANS-IF YOU GO and
NEW ORLEANS-CUISINE.) &QL; 
