<P>
   TEXAS-HICOURT _ Texas Supreme Court issues a ruling in a lawsuit
that challenged the Waco school district's groundbreaking retention
policy, which holds back students who fail the state mandated TAAS
test. Court upheld lower court ruling favoring the school
district's policy but remanded to the lower court a portion of the
lawsuit that questioned if the district violated the Open Meetings
Act in deciding on the policy. By Martha Ashe. File mugs available.
(Waco Tribune-Herald),
