merit some serious attention. &QL; 
It's the kind of attention that prompted Volkswagen to add
odor-control programs in the production of its New Beetle and
latest Golf, and the drive that led Ford to unleash a $75,000
``electronic nose'' to analyze parts for its Focus compact car. By
Tim Moran.
