</P>
<P>
   CAR-SMART-NOSES (Undated) _ Every few days, at precisely the
same hour, a quiet group of experts files into a special room in
Bergen op Zoom in the Netherlands. The white room is built to have
no visual interest at all. The group wears neutral-colored
clothing. They use no makeup, perfume or after-shave before the
meeting _ and have agreed not to eat garlic or spicy foods the
night before. They are the ``expert noses'' for an automotive
supplier, and their job is sniffing plastic to keep foul smells
from becoming part of your car. By Tim Moran.
</P>
