<HEADER>
A2431 &Cx1f; ttd-z
r l BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRO     05-11 0492
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 
 PERSONALS: Thank Heaven for Little Gusts 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
Former Chronicle photographer  &UR; Steve Ringman &LR; 's 17-year-old
snapshot of windblown schoolgirls won $1 million Thursday, May 11,
in a PhotoPoint.com contest.
</P>
<P>
   Ringman, who lives in Seattle, said he saw the girls waiting
outside their church, watched them and ``waited for a gust to
hit.'' Several outraged readers complained about the propriety of
printing this innocent version of the  &UR; Marilyn Monroe &LR;  air-vent
classic.
</P>
<P>
   The Chronicle, which owns part of the picture, will receive 10
percent of the winnings; that portion will be donated to a local
homeless charity.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; HOMAGE TO MOM &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``My mother kept an extra roll of toilet paper that had a little
knit hat and a pompon,''  &UR; Jerry Seinfeld  &LR; told Hollywood On-Line.
``The dog had a sweater, and the couch had little fabric toupees. I
never felt the need to try drugs. My reality was already altered.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. The U.S. Postal Service has created a ``Seinfeld'' stamp,
picturing the apartment shown on the TV show, as part of its Arts &AMP;
Entertainment series of stamps of the '90s. Also honored are
``Titanic'' and ``Jurassic Park,'' and eat your hearts out, poets
and painters.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; THE GREATEST HEROINE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Lucy Lawless &LR; , who plays Xena, Warrior Princess, told Stuff
magazine that she'd prevail in a fight against Wonder Woman. ``Xena
would kick her ass,'' Lawless said, ``because there wasn't a bad
bone in Wonder Woman's body. Xena has base instincts and demons.''
</P>
<P>
   Furthermore, the Bionic Woman ``would run from Xena.'' As for
Buffy the Vampire Slayer, ``What's Buffy got? A wooden stake, some
garlic. Xena has a full arsenal of weapons.''
</P>
<P>
   So who would Xena want in her corner for a tag-team fight?
`` &UR; Judge Judy &LR; ,'' says Lawless. ``She would throw the book at them.
Judge Judy would get them to eat my shorts.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ In Ohio for last weekend's commemoration ceremonies of the
1970 shootings at Kent State University,  &UR; Country Joe McDonald &LR;  and
pals got a ticket for leaving their van unattended at the airport.
It was for $5, and that's what makes it Ohio, love it or leave it.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; _  &UR; Liberace &LR; 's blue-and-white piano, custom-built to play
custom-made rolls, will be sold at Sloan's Auctions in Miami on
Saturday, May 13. The buyer gets the piano plus a video showing
Liberace playing it and explaining how it works. ``It's like having
him in your living room playing the piano!'' says this threatening
press release.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
k2  &LR; WHO SAID WHAT
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``It's my challenge, my spiritual mission to change golf. . .
. &LR; 
 &UR; It's an organic mission.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Johan Lindeberg, &LR;  who created a new clothing collection for
PGA star &UR; Jesper Parnevik. &LR;  Lindeberg is quoted in the menswear
journal DNR.
