 PERSONALS: Thank Heaven for Little Gusts 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle news
file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
Former Chronicle photographer  &UR; Steve Ringman &LR; 's 17-year-old
snapshot of windblown schoolgirls won $1 million Thursday, May 11,
in a PhotoPoint.com contest.
</P>
<P>
   Ringman, who lives in Seattle, said he saw the girls waiting
outside their church, watched them and ``waited for a gust to
hit.'' Several outraged readers complained about the propriety of
printing this innocent version of the  &UR; Marilyn Monroe &LR;  air-vent
classic.
</P>
<P>
   The Chronicle, which owns part of the picture, will receive 10
percent of the winnings; that portion will be donated to a local
homeless charity.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; HOMAGE TO MOM &LR;
