<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS PLAYERS A HIT IN NFL EUROPE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Cowboys wide receiver Jeff Ogden, now a
starring member of the Rhein Fire in NFL Europe, hasn't had nearly
as much trouble catching passes from Danny Wuerffel this spring as
he has had in trying to find a jar of peanut butter in Dusseldorf,
Germany.
</P>
<P>
   Ogden, the Cowboys' fourth or fifth receiver and occasional
return man each of the past two seasons, currently ranks in the top
four among NFL Europe leaders in receptions (20), receiving yards
(276) and a league-high four touchdowns through the first four
weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Cornerback Duane Hawthorne, another Dallas player on loan to NFL
Europe, is tied for the league lead with three interceptions for
the Scottish Claymores.
</P>
<P>
   Ogden and Hawthorne, who are coming off NFL Europe Player of the
Week honors on their respective sides of the ball, meet Saturday
for the league lead in a game to be played at Dusseldorf. Both
teams are 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is like the biggest thing going on here. We feel Ogden is
their go-to guy ... and I'll try not to let him catch too many
passes out there,'' said Hawthorne, who is playing right cornerback
for the Claymores after an impressive 1999 season with three
interceptions for the Cowboys as an undrafted rookie free agent
from Northern Illinois.
</P>
<P>
   Although neither player has Internet access in Europe, Ogden and
Hawthorne are both aware that the Cowboys have made significant
changes at receiver and cornerback.
</P>
<P>
   ``My brother, David, who lives in St. Louis, tells me pretty
much what's going on,'' said Hawthorne. ``Like he told that Kevin
Mathis was gone \Rtraded to New Orleans\S. And as far as \Rthe
Cowboys drafting three cornerbacks\S, I knew that was a key area to
address this off-season. I can't worry about that.''
</P>
<P>
   Both Ogden and Hawthorne welcome the change in being able to
play almost every down in NFL Europe.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are games when I get 70 reps,'' said Ogden, who has
averaged only 10 catches for 103.5 yards and no TDs over the past
two seasons with the Cowboys. ``This allows you to get a feel for
the game. It also eases your anxiety a little bit and allows you to
be more creative out there.''
</P>
<P>
   Ogden will have to vacate his Dusseldorf hotel next week and
move into a ``dorm room at the YMCA or something'' because of
convention coming to town.
</P>
<P>
   So, he plans to take two week's worth of dirty laundry with him
because he hasn't been able to find a laundromat, either.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
