-- Relatives comfort the mother of Ekrem Rexha, known as Commander
Drini, in his hometown of Prizren, Thursday. The former
high-ranking leader of the Kosovo Liberation Army was shot dead
Monday by unknown assailants as he left his home in Prizren outside
his home this week. (Andrew Testa/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- May 11, 2000 -- ATHLETES-CONCUSSIONS -- Eric
Lindros, the Philadelphia Flyers' star center, may not return to
the ice again this season and his athletic future is in doubt
because of concussions he has sustained, the most recent this past
March. Lindros during a game against the New York Rangers in 1997.
(Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) WALTHAM, Mass. -- May 11, 2000 -- SCI-MEDICAL-JOURNAL --
Dr. Jeffrey M. Drazen, seen before a news conference on Thursday,
was named editor-in-chief of the New England Journal of Medicine by
the Massachusetts Medical Society. Drazen has led the Pulmonary
Division at Brigham and Women's since 1989. A specialist in asthma
research, he has written or co-written 200 original research
articles and 100 review articles in medical journals since 1972.
(Evan Richman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) TRENTON, N.J. -- May 11, 2000 -- NJ-SENATE-DEBATE --
Thrilled to get his wealthy opponent out in the open, Jim Florio
tirelessly attacked Jon Corzine on Thursday in the first of their
four debates in the Democratic primary for U.S. Senate. Florio,
right, shakes hands with Corzine before their debate. (Laura
Pedrick/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
