-- The body of Kosovo Liberation Army leader Ekrem Rexha, known by
his codename ``Drini,'' in the courtyard of his house in Prizren
before his burial on Thursday. One of the most influential KLA
commanders during the war with Serbia, Rexha was shot dead Monday
by unknown assailants as he left his home in Prizren to go to work
at the council offices, where he was responsible for environmental
and civil security issues. (Andrew Testa/The New York Times) LITE
