BBO-SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN-BOS -- Baseballs are flying out of major
league parks at a record clip and the usual conspiracy theories are
being raised. Baseball commissioner Bud Selig has commissioned a
scientific study to determine if today's baseballs conform to size,
weight, and impact standards established by Major League Baseball.
Professor Jim Sherwood of the University of Massachusetts in
Lowell, Mass., and Patrick Drane prepare a bat and ball for testing
at the Baseball Research center at U-Mass. (Bill Greene/Boston
Globe Photo)
</P>
