Rockefeller Center, famous for the 100-foot Christmas tree it
erects every year, will have another large but definitely cuter
silhouette to take its place in the next few weeks. ``Puppy,'' by
Jeff Koons, a 43-foot terrier puppy made of flowers, will go up in
front of 30 Rockefeller Plaza, the same spot where the tree is
installed in December. Koons sculpture in the courtyard of a palace
in Arolsen, Germany, in 1992. (Public Art Fund/The New York Times)
