<P>
   (NYT7) UNDATED -- May 11, 2000 -- FORD-SUVS -- Ford Motor Co.,
the world's No. 2 automaker, on Thursday conceded for the first
time that its popular -- but gas-guzzling -- sport utility
vehicles, including the Ford Excursion, seen here, pose problems
for a company that wants to be known as an environmental leader.
Ford, in a 98-page corporate citizenship report presented during
its annual shareholders meeting Thursday, said its market
leadership in sport utility vehicles, the most profitable group of
vehicles Ford sells, has created a dilemma for the company as it
works to be a leader in improving fuel economy and cutting
emissions. (Norman Y. Lono/The New York Times)
</P>
