good'' friend, ``more now than maybe I did before.'' Nathan speaks
to reporters Wednesday night. (Aaron Lee Fineman/The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) NEW YORK -- May 11, 2000 -- NY-GIULIANI -- Mayor Rudolph
Giuliani announced Wednesday that he was separating from his wife
Donna Hanover. In a news conference hours later, Hanover said their
relationship was difficult ``because of his relationship with one
staff member.'' Friends of Hanover said that Hanover was referring
to a relationship between her husband and Cristyne F. Lategano,
Giuliani's former communications director. Lategano, left, and
Giuliani before a news conference in March. (Don Hogan Charles/The
New York Times)
