Rodham Clinton, running for the U.S. Senate seat from New York,
reacts to a supporter soon to graduate from college sporting his
gown and a sign wishing her a happy Mother's Day outside the
studios of the Today Show on Rockefeller Center where she was
interviewed, Thursday. Clinton made it clear during the interview
that she will not make any pronouncements about the turmoil
involving Mayor Rudolph Giuliani's personal life. The viability of
the mayor's Senate campaign was jeopardized by his disclosure
Wednesday that he and his wife, Donna Hanover, are discussing a
separation. (James Estrin/The New York Times)
</P>
