<HEADLINE>
Y&AMP;R CHIEF EXPECTED TO STEP DOWN AFTER MERGER WITH WPP 
</HEADLINE>
   By ANDREW ROSS SORKIN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON _ Young &AMP; Rubicam's president and chief executive, Thomas
D. Bell Jr., will most likely step down from the advertising agency
after it is acquired by WPP Group, executives close to the
negotiations said early Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Both advertising companies were working into the early morning
to formalize WPP's acquisition of Y&AMP;R, one of the last independent
advertising agencies, in hopes of formally announcing the deal
before the stock market opens in London on Friday, the executives
said.
</P>
<P>
   Y&AMP;R's annual meeting will take place Friday in New York.
</P>
<P>
   The companies agreed in principle earlier this week to merge,
although they have not announced the deal. As agreed to earlier in
the week, WPP will pay 0.835 American depository receipt for each
share of Y&AMP;R While the value of the acquisition has become a moving
target because the stocks of both companies have fluctuated, as of
Thursday the deal was worth $4.8 billion, down $900 million from
when the companies agreed in principle to the arrangement.
</P>
<P>
   While Bell will play a prominent role in the integration of the
two companies by sitting on a four-person transition committee, he
has told executives he has decided to leave once the merger is
complete.
</P>
<P>
   According to executives close to the talks, Bell originally
spurned an acquisition by Martin Sorrell, WPP's chief executive,
but later decided it was strategically sound. He also declined an
offer by Y&AMP;R's board to make the acquisition conditional upon his
employment in a job of his choosing, the executives said.
</P>
<P>
   Several executives said that his relationship with Sorrell had
soured during the earlier negotiations but that over the last week
the two had become friendlier.
</P>
<P>
   Bell has been chief executive of Y&AMP;R only since January. Before
that, he served as chairman and chief executive of Young &AMP; Rubicam
Advertising, the company's flagship agency. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
